-- Thailand Stocks: PTT Exploration, Quality Houses, Sahaviriya
-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 2012-06-06T09:48:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-06/advanced-info-sahaviriya-total-access-thailand-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in  Thailand   trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Bangkok. The  SET
Index (SET)  rose 1.7 percent to 1,117.95, the largest increase since
Feb. 15.  Oil companies :  PTT Pcl (PTT)  , Thailand’s largest energy
company, climbed 1.7 percent to 308 baht, the first advance in
three days.  PTT Exploration & Production Pcl (PTTEP)  ,
Thailand’s only publicly traded oil explorer, gained 1.6 percent
to 157.50 baht.  Oil for July delivery rose for a third day, climbing as
much as $1.10 to $85.39 a barrel in  New York .  Quality Houses Pcl (QH)  , a property developer, added 2.8
percent to 1.48 baht, the biggest gain since May 10. The company
plans to raise about 2 billion baht ($63.6 million) from a
property fund, Senior Executive Vice President Suwanna
Buddhaprasart told investors in Bangkok today.  Sahaviriya Steel Industries Pcl (SSI)  , the country’s
biggest steelmaker, advanced 1.5 percent to 0.66 baht, the first
increase in four days. The company raised 600 million baht
selling convertible bonds to a group of investors, it said in a
regulatory filing today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
